Hello Amala, I'm going to +2 but I really like to see a test result around this fix to make my confidence. I see you remove the testing because reason [1], that just is my question here: I see #1261376 been marked to "invalid", and seems the "reset()" will never be added to oslo.config, so may I know your test case plan for this patch? Thanks.

Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I have to echo Zhi Yan Liu's sentiments here. The bug in oslo has been marked as Invalid so I don't really understand the justification for not providing tests.

Patch Set 7:

If I understand the issue correctly, the thing to do is just to unregister the opts after the test runs.  Just because reset() doesn't do what is needed doesn't mean it's impossible to write tests for this.

Patch Set 7:

Hi,
Thanks for all the reviews. The issue here is that the config options just dont get reset. Initial understanding was that unregister_opts() would take care of that bit, but apparently it doesn't. I can manually reset the config and jenkins would be happy, but I'd noticed something weird in the logs, all the migrations were being run in the unit test. This clearly indicated how the config resets were messing up the configs set for the other tests. Thoughts?
